'''''We the Corporations: How American Businesses Won Their Civil Rights''''' is a book-length history of American [[corporate personhood]] and other rights of [[corporations]] written by [[constitutional law]] professor [[Adam Winkler]] and published by [[W. W. Norton]] in 2018.

The title was a [[2018 National Book Award for Nonfiction]] finalist.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Grady |first1=Constance |title=The 2018 National Book Award finalists are in. Heres the full list. |work=[[Vox (website)|Vox]] |date=2018-10-10 |url=https://www.vox.com/culture/2018/10/10/17959504/2018-national-book-award-finalists |accessdate=2018-11-13 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>

